# Agent Workflow Rules (Next.js Vibe Engineering)

## Agent Boundaries

### Agent 00: Figma Analyzer
- **Does:** Accept Figma URL + Frame name, use Figma MCP to extract specs, save to `.cursornext/cache/figma-specs-{feature}.md`. Extract hierarchy, measurements, colors, typography, spacing; map to Next.js (COLORS, TYPOGRAPHY/FONTS, spacing). When icons/vectors are present, export required SVGs (via Figma MCP export or Figma REST API with `FIGMA_ACCESS_TOKEN`) to `.cursornext/cache/figma-svgs/{feature}/` so development can use them directly (as SVG React components or in `public/`).
- **Setup:** Set `FIGMA_ACCESS_TOKEN` in **`.env`** in the project root (never `.env.local` or `.env.example`; never commit the token). See agent-00-figma-analyzer.md for details.
- **Does not:** Create PRD, write code, or proceed to next agent automatically.
- **Stops when:** Specs file is saved. Invoke: `@figma-analyzer` with Feature name, Figma URL + Frame, Section.

### Agent 01: Planning Agent
- **Does:** Read Figma specs or prompt, create PRD with communication history, save to `.cursornext/logs/prd-{feature}-{timestamp}.md`.
- **Does not:** Write code or run tests.
- **Stops when:** PRD is saved. Invoke: `@planning-agent` with prompt or path to specs.

### Agent 02: Coding Agent
- **Does:** Read PRD, load rules/skills, implement code (App Router routes, components, services, store), update coding log, run lint/typecheck/build validation.
- **Does not:** Create PRD or run E2E tests.
- **Stops when:** Code is implemented and log updated. Invoke: `@coding-agent` with PRD path.

### Agent 03: Documentation Agent
- **Does:** Add JSDoc/TSDoc, file headers, inline comments.
- **Does not:** Change logic or add features.
- **Stops when:** Documentation added. Invoke: `@documentation-agent`.

### Agent 04: Fixing Agent
- **Does:** Fix issues from user prompt; read code/coding log, apply fixes, save fixing log to `.cursornext/logs/fixing/fixing-{feature}.md`. When testing is requested: require test-cases file (`.cursornext/logs/test-cases-{feature}.md`); run Jest + React Testing Library (and E2E via Playwright if configured), track results by test case ID and priority, fix simple failures, re-run failed tests, document in same fixing log.
- **Does not:** Create PRD or implement new features.
- **Stops when:** Fixes applied and log updated (and tests run + results documented if test-and-fix). Invoke: `@fixing-agent` with feature name or "Test {feature}". Test cases template: `.cursornext/rules/log-templates/test-cases-template.md`. **E2E (Playwright):** config `playwright.config.ts`, specs `e2e/**/*.spec.ts`, commands `npm run e2e`; see `.cursornext/docs/E2E-PLAYWRIGHT.md` and `.cursornext/rules/e2e-testing.mdc`.

### Agent 05: Code Scanning Agent
- **Does:** Run quality checklist, run ESLint (`next lint`) + TypeScript check (and SonarQube if configured), document findings, save report to `.cursornext/logs/code-scanning/`.
- **Does not:** Fix code.
- **Stops when:** Report saved. Invoke: `@code-scanning-agent`.

### Agent 06: Vulnerability Agent
- **Does:** Run npm audit (and Snyk if configured), categorize by severity (P1–P4), document prioritized remediation, save report to `.cursornext/logs/vulnerability/`.
- **Does not:** Apply fixes.
- **Stops when:** Report saved. Invoke: `@vulnerability-agent`.

### Agent 07: PR Orchestrator Agent
- **Does:** Collect PRD, coding log, fixing log, scans; generate PR document.
- **Does not:** Submit or merge PR.
- **Stops when:** PR document saved. Invoke: `@pr-orchestrator-agent`.

### Agent 08: Project Scaffold Agent
- **Does:** Create a new Next.js project with **given app name** via `create-next-app` (TypeScript, App Router, ESLint), then add **folder structure + boilerplate**. Scaffolds src/ (app, components/layouts, components/widgets, constants, theme, hooks, services, lib, api, store, types, utils, styles, assets/icons), theme tokens (COLORS/TYPOGRAPHY/spacing), root layout + providers, one sample route (Home), one Redux slice (common), **`.env`** (only env file — no `.env.local` / `.env.example`), the **dependency-free fetch client** (`src/lib/fetch-client.ts`, axios-free) via `pnpm setup:fetch`, and **error pages** (Connection Lost + Unauthorized + NetworkGate + AppShell) via `node .cursornext/scripts/setup-error-pages.js`. **No axios.** Saves log to `.cursornext/logs/project-scaffold/project-scaffold-{name}-{timestamp}.md`.
- **Does not:** Deploy; does not create the project inside the workspace (creates sibling folder).
- **Stops when:** Project created via CLI and boilerplate added; log saved. Invoke: `@project-scaffold-agent` with app name.

### Agent 09: Prompt Generator Agent
- **Does:** Two modes. (A) Read **business brief** (YAML) and optionally **Figma specs**; generate **prompt for the Planning Agent**; save to `.cursornext/cache/prompt-{feature}.md`. (B) Generate **project creation prompt** (Next.js + TypeScript + standard boilerplate); save to `.cursornext/cache/prompt-project-create-{name}.md`.
- **Does not:** Create PRD or write code; does not run create-next-app or Figma MCP (specs must already be in cache from Figma Analyzer if used for mode A).
- **Stops when:** Prompt file is saved. Invoke: `@prompt-generator-agent` with feature name (mode A) or project name + "TypeScript and boilerplate" (mode B).

### Agent 10: Test Case Authoring Agent
- **Does:** Create manual QA test cases + automated Jest + React Testing Library test files for a feature. Bridges Planning/Coding outputs and Fixing Agent inputs.
- **Does not:** Run Playwright E2E tests or fix code.
- **Stops when:** Test cases file and Jest test file created. Invoke: `@testcases-agent` with feature name + PRD/coding log paths.

### Agent 11: Playwright E2E Testing Agent
- **Does:** Create Playwright E2E spec files for a route/flow or entire app (if not created), run Playwright tests with screenshot/trace/video capture, generate detailed test reports with artifacts organized in folders (screenshots, videos, traces, test-results.md).
- **Does not:** Fix code, create PRD, or implement features.
- **Stops when:** Tests executed, artifacts organized, test results document generated. Invoke: `@e2e-testing-agent` with feature name (or "entire app") + base URL (e.g. http://localhost:3000). **E2E (Playwright):** config `playwright.config.ts`, specs `e2e/**/*.spec.ts`, commands `npm run e2e`; see `.cursornext/docs/E2E-PLAYWRIGHT.md` and `.cursornext/rules/e2e-testing.mdc`.

### Agent 12: Pre-PR Validation Agent
- **Does:** Review **only the changed files** (git diff vs base branch; default `main`) and related dependents (for breaking-change context) before a PR. Validates code quality & best practices, folder-structure compliance, React/Next.js performance (Server/Client split, `next/image`, memoization), security/insecure patterns, TypeScript/lint/test/build (scoped), PR readiness, and potential breaking changes. Runs scoped ESLint/type check/build/Jest, produces P1/P2/P3 findings and a **READY / NOT READY** verdict. Saves report to `.cursornext/logs/pre-pr/pre-pr-{branch-or-feature}-{timestamp}.md`. **Recommendations only — does not modify code.**
- **Does not:** Fix/refactor code, create PRD, implement/scaffold, or create/commit/submit/merge a PR.
- **Stops when:** Report saved and verdict announced. Invoke: `@pre-pr-validation-agent` (optional base branch). Run **before** `@pr-orchestrator-agent`; hand off fixes to `@fixing-agent` / `@coding-agent`.

### Agent 13: useForm Builder Agent
- **Does:** Build or refactor a form using the project's schema-based **`useForm`** hook — field handlers, dirty-gated errors, i18n error messages (`ALERTS`/`TITLES`), shared validators in `constants/form-validators`, service-layer submit (`.then()/.catch()`). Installs the hook via `pnpm setup:useform` (or `node .cursor/scripts/setup-useform.js`) if missing. Updates coding log at `.cursornext/logs/coding/coding-{feature}.md`.
- **Does not:** Create PRD, run E2E, or add new form libraries (no Formik/react-hook-form/yup).
- **Stops when:** Form works, typecheck/lint pass, coding log updated. Invoke: `@useform-builder-agent` with form name + fields + target path. See `.cursornext/rules/useform-validation.mdc`; hook templates in `.cursornext/setup/hooks/`.

### Agent 14: Monorepo Scaffold Agent
- **Does:** Create a **new pnpm workspace monorepo** (apps + shared `ui`/`lib-utils` packages) via `node .cursornext/scripts/setup-monorepo.js`. Uses **pnpm workspaces only** (no Turborepo unless `USE_TURBO=true`). Creates each Next.js app via `create-next-app`, copies the kit into the new repo as `.cursor/`, creates root **`.env`** (only env file), installs `useForm` and the **dependency-free fetch client** (`packages/lib-utils/src/lib/fetch-client.ts`, axios-free) into `packages/lib-utils`, installs the example module into the primary app, runs `pnpm install`. Saves log to `.cursornext/logs/monorepo-scaffold/monorepo-{name}-{timestamp}.md`.
- **Does not:** Build features, create PRD, deploy, or run Figma MCP. **Not** for single apps — use `@project-scaffold-agent` for one app.
- **Stops when:** Monorepo created, `pnpm install` succeeds, log saved. Invoke: `@monorepo-scaffold-agent` with monorepo name (+ optional apps/packages/turbo).

### Agent 15: Fetch Client Setup Agent
- **Does:** Install and wire the **dependency-free `fetch`-based HTTP client** (axios-free) into a project or shared package via `pnpm setup:fetch` (`FETCH_TARGET=packages/lib-utils` for monorepos). Configures `baseURL` (`NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL`) + request/response interceptors (auth token, language, 401/403), points services at `@/lib/fetch-client` (`http`), converts direct axios usage (incl. uploads → `uploadFile`) to the client, and removes axios from `package.json` where unused. The client mirrors the axios response/error shape so `.then()/.catch()` services keep working. Saves coding log to `.cursornext/logs/coding/coding-fetch-client.md`.
- **Does not:** Create PRD, implement product features, add a third-party HTTP library, or run E2E.
- **Stops when:** Fetch client installed + wired, axios removed where unused, validation passes, log saved. Invoke: `@fetch-client-agent` (optional target + interceptor needs). See `.cursornext/agents/agent-15-fetch-client.md`.

### Agent 16: User Story Test Case Generator
- **Does:** Generate flow-based manual QA test cases from a **user story description** alone (no PRD or coding log required). Saves to `.cursornext/logs/test-cases-{feature}.md` with TC-IDs, priorities, flows, `data-testid` selectors, and Jest/Playwright mapping hints for downstream agents.
- **Does not:** Write feature code, run tests, or create Jest/Playwright files (use Agent 10 for Jest; Agent 11 for Playwright).
- **Stops when:** Test cases file is saved. Invoke: `@user-story-testcases-agent` with feature name + user story text (or path). See `.cursornext/agents/agent-16-user-story-testcases.md`.

### Agent 17: Unit Test Analysis Agent
- **Does:** Perform **code-driven** unit test analysis on an implemented Next.js page, component, or feature module — inventory inputs/events/validations, build coverage matrix, detect bugs, and generate production-ready Jest + React Testing Library tests. Saves report to `.cursornext/logs/unit-test-analysis/unit-test-analysis-{feature}-{timestamp}.md` and Jest file to `__tests__/{Feature}.test.tsx` (unless `analysis only`).
- **Does not:** Fix production code, run Playwright E2E, or create PRD.
- **Stops when:** Report saved, Jest file written (unless opted out), and summary posted. Invoke: `@unit-test-analysis-agent` with target name + optional scope. See `.cursornext/agents/agent-17-unit-test-analysis.md`.

### Agent 18: npm Audit Auto-Fix Agent
- **Does:** Automatically scan and fix npm vulnerabilities (low, moderate, high, critical) via `node .cursornext/scripts/npm-audit-auto-fix.js`. Triggered by the `afterShellExecution` hook after `npm install` / `npm ci`, or invoked manually. Saves report to `.cursornext/logs/vulnerability/npm-audit-auto-fix-{timestamp}.md`.
- **Does not:** Replace Agent 06 documentation-only scans; does not implement product features.
- **Stops when:** Audit + fix run complete and report saved. Invoke: `@npm-audit-auto-fix-agent` (or automatic after `npm install`). See `.cursornext/agents/agent-18-npm-audit-auto-fix.md`.

### Agent 19: Error Pages Setup Agent
- **Does:** Install **Connection Lost** and **Unauthorized (Not Authorized)** error pages with global offline handling via `node .cursornext/scripts/setup-error-pages.js`. Adds layouts, `NetworkGate` + `AppShell` in `layout.tsx`, browser `useNetworkStatus`, `/unauthorized` route, `handleUnauthorized`, and constants. **Runs automatically during project scaffold (Agent 08) and monorepo scaffold (Agent 14).** Saves coding log to `.cursornext/logs/coding/coding-error-pages.md`.
- **Does not:** Create PRD; implement auth/login flow; run `npm run dev`.
- **Stops when:** Setup complete, wiring verified, log saved. Invoke: `@error-pages-agent`. See `.cursornext/agents/agent-19-error-pages.md`.

---

## Workflow Sequence

0. **Project Scaffold Agent** (optional) → New **single** Next.js app with app name + folder structure + boilerplate → `.cursornext/logs/project-scaffold/project-scaffold-{name}-{timestamp}.md`
0b. **Monorepo Scaffold Agent** (optional, instead of 0 for multi-app) → New pnpm workspace monorepo (apps + shared packages) → `.cursornext/logs/monorepo-scaffold/monorepo-{name}-{timestamp}.md`
1. **Figma Analyzer** → `.cursornext/cache/figma-specs-{feature}.md`
1b. **Business brief** (developer fills) → `.cursornext/setup/business-briefs/business-brief-{feature}.yaml`
1c. **Prompt Generator Agent** (optional) → Reads brief + Figma specs → `.cursornext/cache/prompt-{feature}.md` (use this as input to Planning Agent)
2. **Planning Agent** → `.cursornext/logs/prd-{feature}-{timestamp}.md`
3. **Coding Agent** → Code + `.cursornext/logs/coding/coding-{feature}.md`
3b. **useForm Builder Agent** (optional, for forms) → Form built with `useForm` + coding log
3c. **Fetch Client Setup Agent** (optional; scaffold agents already install it) → `src/lib/fetch-client.ts` wired (axios-free) + `.cursornext/logs/coding/coding-fetch-client.md`
3d. **Error Pages Setup Agent** (optional; scaffold agents already install it) → Connection Lost + Unauthorized + NetworkGate + AppShell → `.cursornext/logs/coding/coding-error-pages.md`
4. **Documentation Agent** → Comments + doc log
4a. **User Story Test Case Generator** (optional, story-only — no PRD) → `.cursornext/logs/test-cases-{feature}.md`
5. **Test Case Authoring Agent** (optional) → `.cursornext/logs/test-cases-{feature}.md` + `__tests__/{Feature}.test.tsx`
5b. **Unit Test Analysis Agent** (optional, code-driven) → `.cursornext/logs/unit-test-analysis/unit-test-analysis-{feature}-{timestamp}.md` + `__tests__/{Feature}.test.tsx`
6. **Playwright E2E Testing Agent** (optional) → E2E tests + artifacts (screenshots/, videos/, traces/, test-results.md) at `.cursornext/logs/e2e-testing/{feature}/{timestamp}/`
7. **Fixing Agent** → Fixes + `.cursornext/logs/fixing/fixing-{feature}.md`
8. **Code Scanning Agent** → `.cursornext/logs/code-scanning/`
9. **Vulnerability Agent** → `.cursornext/logs/vulnerability/`
9b. **npm Audit Auto-Fix Agent** (optional; auto after `npm install`) → `.cursornext/logs/vulnerability/npm-audit-auto-fix-{timestamp}.md`
10. **Pre-PR Validation Agent** (before PR) → `.cursornext/logs/pre-pr/pre-pr-{feature}-{timestamp}.md`
11. **PR Orchestrator Agent** → `.cursornext/logs/pr/pr-{feature}-{timestamp}.md`

Each step requires manual invocation except where an agent explicitly calls another (e.g. Planning does not auto-call Coding).

---

## Invocation (Explicit)

- `@project-scaffold-agent` — App name (e.g. MyApp, DashboardPro) — Creates a **single** project with folder structure + boilerplate
- `@monorepo-scaffold-agent` — Monorepo name (+ optional apps/packages/turbo) — Creates a pnpm workspace monorepo (apps + shared packages)
- `@prompt-generator-agent` — Feature name (mode A) or project name + "TypeScript and boilerplate" (mode B)
- `@figma-analyzer` — Feature name, Figma URL + Frame, Section
- `@planning-agent` — Use prompt or path to specs/PRD
- `@coding-agent` — Implement PRD from [prd-file]
- `@useform-builder-agent` — Build/validate a form with the `useForm` hook (form name + fields + target path)
- `@fetch-client-agent` — Install/wire the dependency-free fetch HTTP client (axios-free); replace axios; configure interceptors
- `@error-pages-agent` — Install Connection Lost + Unauthorized error pages with global offline handling (browser online/offline events + NetworkGate)
- `@documentation-agent` — Document the code
- `@user-story-testcases-agent` — Feature name + user story → manual QA test cases (no PRD required)
- `@testcases-agent` — Feature name + PRD/coding log paths — Creates test cases + Jest tests
- `@unit-test-analysis-agent` — Target page/component name — Code-driven analysis + Jest tests + bug report
- `@e2e-testing-agent` — Feature name (or "entire app") + base URL — Creates Playwright tests, runs E2E, captures screenshots/videos/traces, generates reports
- `@fixing-agent` — Feature name or description of what to fix
- `@code-scanning-agent` — Scan quality for [feature]
- `@vulnerability-agent` — Scan security
- `@npm-audit-auto-fix-agent` — Auto-fix npm vulnerabilities (also runs after `npm install` via hook)
- `@pre-pr-validation-agent` — Validate only changed files before a PR (quality, structure, performance, security, TS/lint/test/build, PR readiness, breaking changes) + READY/NOT READY verdict
- `@pr-orchestrator-agent` — Create PR for [feature]

One agent, one task, one stop. Human approval at each step.
